A man and a woman were being questioned by police on suspicion of murder tonight after a body was discovered in a quiet village street.

Police were called to a house in Pyle, South Wales at 6am today where officers found the body of a 46-year-old man.

A 41-year-old woman, who lives in the village, and a 52-year-old man from Porthcawl were arrested shortly afterwards and were being questioned at a police station in Bridgend tonight.

